747	\subsection{The second Mathlib gap: $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\PreservesMonomorphisms$}
748	\label{sec:hmodule_prime_module_free_preserves_mono_gap}
749	
750	Mathlib's \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/Grp/Adjunctions.lean} registers the instance \lstinline{AddCommGrpCat.instPreservesMonomorphismsFree : AddCommGrpCat.free.PreservesMonomorphisms}. The corresponding instance for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavour is \emph{absent} from \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean}. Without it, after \lstinline{simp only [biprod.lift_snd]} the residual goal $\mathtt{Mono}\,(-(\presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathtt{map}\,(\mathtt{Functor.whiskerRight}\,(\yoneda.\mathtt{map}\,S.f_{13})\,(\ModuleCat.\free\,k)))$ cannot be discharged by \lstinline{infer_instance} (probe-verified by the iter-020 plan-agent: synthesis fails outright).
751	
752	\begin{definition}[Helper instance: $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$ preserves monomorphisms (iter-020)]
753	  \label{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}
754	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}
755	  \uses{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
756	  \leanok
757	  Working over a field $k$, the free-module functor $\ModuleCat.\free\,k : \mathrm{Type}\,u \to \ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$ preserves monomorphisms: for any injective function $f : X \to Y$ between types, $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\mathtt{map}\,f$ is injective on $\Finsupp\,X\,k$.
758	\end{definition}
759	
760	\begin{proof}
761	  \leanok
762	  Mathlib's \lstinline{Finsupp.mapDomain_injective} (\texttt{Mathlib/Data/Finsupp/Basic.lean}) provides the underlying-set-level proof: if $f : X \to Y$ is injective, then $\Finsupp.\mathtt{mapDomain}\,f : \Finsupp\,X\,k \to \Finsupp\,Y\,k$ is injective. Combined with $\ModuleCat.\mathtt{mono\_iff\_injective}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/EpiMono.lean}) bridging \lstinline{Mono} in $\ModuleCat\,k$ to underlying-set injectivity, and $\CategoryTheory.\mathtt{mono\_iff\_injective}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Types/Basic.lean}) bridging \lstinline{Mono} in $\mathrm{Type}\,u$ to underlying-set injectivity, the preservation predicate reduces to a four-line tactic block. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms it typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + post-iter-019 project state, kernel-only axioms.
763	\end{proof}
