836	\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES connecting hom (iter-021)}
837	
838	After Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_shortExact} (the iter-020 short-exact predicate on the iter-019 short complex) the named lemma $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{shortExact}\,k\,S$ exposes an extension class $\mathtt{extClass} : \Ext\,(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).X_1\,(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).X_3\,1$ (Mathlib \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/DerivedCategory/Ext/ExactSequences.lean}). Iter-021 uses it to build the connecting homomorphism $\delta : H^{n_0}(S.X_1) \to H^{n_1}(S.X_4)$ of the Mayer-Vietoris long exact sequence in $\ModuleCat\,k$-valued sheaf cohomology, mirroring Mathlib \texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/MayerVietoris.lean} L112--114.
839	
840	\begin{definition}[Connecting homomorphism $\delta$ of the MV-LES (iter-021)]
841	  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_delta}
842	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_δ}
843	  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_shortExact, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_cohomologyPresheaf}
844	  \leanok
845	  Let $k$ be a field, $C$ a category equipped with a Grothendieck topology $J$ on which $\HasWeakSheafify\,J\,(\Type\,u)$, $\HasSheafify\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, and $\HasExt\,(\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k))$ all hold. Let $S : J.\MayerVietorisSquare$ be a Mayer-Vietoris square, $F : \Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$, and $n_0, n_1 \in \mathbb N$ with $n_0 + 1 = n_1$. The \emph{connecting homomorphism} of the Mayer-Vietoris LES at degree $(n_0, n_1)$ is
846	  \[
847	    \HModulePrime\_\delta : (\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{cohomologyPresheaf}\,k\,F\,n_0).\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\,S.X_1)
848	      \;\longrightarrow\;
