\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES exactness theorem and $\delta$-zero $\mathtt{simp}$ companions (iter-026)}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime_mayer_vietoris_exact}

Iter-026 is the keystone of the Mayer-Vietoris LES build-out: the exactness theorem for the iter-022 sequence, plus two $\delta$-zero $\mathtt{simp}$ companions ($\delta \circ \toBiprod = 0$ and $\fromBiprod \circ \delta = 0$) that are immediate corollaries of exactness.

\begin{theorem}[Mayer-Vietoris LES exactness ($\HModulePrime$ flavor, iter-026)]
  \label{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_sequence_exact}
  \leanok
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequenceIso}
  In the setting of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence}, the iter-022 LES sequence is exact:
  \[
    (\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence}\,k\,S\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h).\Exact.
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequenceIso}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{MayerVietorisSquare.sequence\_exact}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L140--141). Apply $\ComposableArrows.\mathtt{exact\_of\_iso}$ with the inverse of the iter-023 comparison iso $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequenceIso}$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequenceIso}) to transport exactness from $\Ext.\contravariantSequence$ — which is exact by Mathlib's $\Abelian.\Ext.\contravariantSequence\_\mathtt{exact}$. One-liner body:
  \begin{lstlisting}
  ComposableArrows.exact_of_iso (HModule'_sequenceIso k S F n₀ n₁ h).symm
    (Abelian.Ext.contravariantSequence_exact _ _ _ _ _)
  \end{lstlisting}
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\delta \circ \toBiprod = 0$ ($\mathtt{simp}$ companion, iter-026)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_delta_toBiprod}
