    \;=\; 0.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L143--145. Immediate from the third zero-composition (index 2) of the iter-022 sequence's exactness: $(\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence\_exact}\,k\,S\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h).\mathtt{zero}\,2$. The \lstinline{@[reassoc (attr := simp)]} attribute generates the post-composition variant and registers the lemma as a $\mathtt{simp}$-set member, both load-bearing for downstream Mayer-Vietoris consumers.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\fromBiprod \circ \delta = 0$ ($\mathtt{simp}$ companion, iter-026)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_delta}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_fromBiprod_δ}
  \leanok
  \uses{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
