    \;=\; 0.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L147--149. Immediate from the second zero-composition (index 1) of the iter-022 sequence's exactness: $(\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence\_exact}\,k\,S\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h).\mathtt{zero}\,1$. Same $\mathtt{simp}$ attribute as Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_delta_toBiprod}.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[Build-out completion]
  Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact} together with Lemmas~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_delta_toBiprod} and~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_delta} closes out the iter-016 $\to$ iter-026 cohort. The full Mayer-Vietoris LES infrastructure for $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$-valued cohomology now mirrors Mathlib's $\AddCommGrpCat$-flavored MV-LES line-by-line, with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \rightarrow \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. Iter-027 then split this build-out off into the present chapter, leaving Chapter~\ref{chap:Cohomology_StructureSheafModuleK} hosting only the carriers $\HModule$, $\HModulePrime$, the iter-006 structure-sheaf-as-$\ModuleCat\,k$-sheaf $\toModuleKSheaf$, and the iter-012 Čech scaffolding. The MV-LES is now ready to be specialised in iter-028+ to a 2-affine cover of a proper $k$-curve, which is the engine of the queued Serre-finiteness theorem $\Module.\Finite\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n)$ that $\mathtt{smoothOfRelativeDimension\_genus}$ will eventually consume.
\end{remark>

